===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}

{{liushu|p}} – human eye, now rotated 90 degrees. Compare the Egyptian hieroglyph {{m|egy|𓁹}}.

See also [[直]], [[見]], [[頁]], [[夏]], [[面]], {{zh-l|*臣}} and the earlier versions of [[要]]. The eye is not rotated in the character {{zh-l|*𢛳}}, [[曼]], [[睪]], and [[眔]] (used in [[褱]]).

Sometimes it depicts a web ([[网]]) through its variant [[罒]], e.g., [[買]], [[罵]], [[罪]], [[詈]] (used in [[罰]]) and [[羅]] (> [[罗]]). Unrelated to [[鼎]], [[貝]], and [[真]].

===Etymology===
From {{inh|zh|sit-pro|*mjək}}. Cognate with {{cog|bo|མིག||eye}}, {{cog|my|မျက်||eye, face}}.

